      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CRAFTY CHAP (5) jumps from box 5 again after finishing a 4.5 lengths third (30.45) last time at Wentworth Park over 520m. Safe beginner but tricky box to overcome. Well worth another try. DANDY REDEEMER (2) missed the frame last time but prior to that was an effortless Grade 5 winner (23.44) at this track, scoring by 4.5 lengths. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the low draw. Can turn it around this time. MIDNIGHT STAR (1) settled down midfield and held her position to the line when finishing 5th (18.59) at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning seven races. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Key player if finds best. SOUL PANORAMIC (3) cannot be left out over a shorter distance.",
